                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29882",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=silvan",
                        "name": "silvan",
                        "displayName": "Silvan Zurbruegg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "patch for Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Abstract.php.\n\ncontains missing function exec()",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=silvan",
                        "name": "silvan",
                        "displayName": "Silvan Zurbruegg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-02T01:35:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-02T01:35:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29883",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=silvan",
                        "name": "silvan",
                        "displayName": "Silvan Zurbruegg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "unittests for \/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/TestCommon.php\n\nunittests for exec() method.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=silvan",
                        "name": "silvan",
                        "displayName": "Silvan Zurbruegg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-02T01:36:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-02T01:36:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30197",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just for my information, why don't you want to use the query() method? (except to retrieve number of rows)\n\nWith you proposition, there is also no profiling.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T00:43:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T00:43:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30199",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsmith",
                        "name": "lsmith",
                        "displayName": "Lukas Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Two reasons:\n1) for certain queries you dont need a result set and therefore creating the statement instance is needless overhead\n2) exec() returns the number of affected rows, that I would have to get with another method call if I were to use query()",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsmith",
                        "name": "lsmith",
                        "displayName": "Lukas Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T01:24:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T01:24:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30200",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsmith",
                        "name": "lsmith",
                        "displayName": "Lukas Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Also semantically it is important to know that this is not a select query, for example if one would want to run an explain automatically. These are also usually not the type of queries that need profiling and if they do .. though I invite you to add profiling support.\n\nFinally the lack of the exec() method prevents Zend_Db to work as a drop in replacement for PDO projects.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsmith",
                        "name": "lsmith",
                        "displayName": "Lukas Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T01:26:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T01:26:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30202",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks Lukas.\n\nRalph, I can apply the patch and test it against all PDO adapters with limitation mentions above => no profiling.\n\nYour opinion?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-17T03:59:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-17T03:59:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30452",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch applied to trunk and 1.8 release branch.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-26T18:57:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-26T18:57:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30471",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Modified in SVN15204\n\nTested with all adapters:\n{code}\nPHPUnit 3.3.15 by Sebastian Bergmann.\n\nZend Framework - Zend_Db\n Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_MssqlTest\n ...\n\n Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_MysqlTest\n ...\n\n Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_OciTest\n ...\n\n Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_PgsqlTest\n ..F\n\n Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_SqliteTest\n ...\n\nTime: 10 seconds\n\nThere was 1 failure:\n\n1) testAdapterExecModifiedNone(Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_PgsqlTest)\nExpected exec() to return zero affected rows; got 1\nFailed asserting that <integer:1> matches expected value <integer:0>.\nexpected integer <0>\ndifference       <1>\ngot integer      <1>\n\nFAILURES!\nTests: 15, Assertions: 15, Failures: 1.\n{code}\n\nPgsql seems to always return true instead of the number of affected rows (tested with another query).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-27T11:42:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-27T11:43:02.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
